# @plurnk/plurnk-mimetypes-embeddings — configuration knobs.
# The host process sets these in its environment; this file is the contract.

# PLURNK_EMBED_WORKERS — REQUIRED, no default. embedBatch() pool size: how many
# single-threaded workers texts are spread across. Each worker holds its own
# model copy, so this is a memory↔throughput decision only you can make — the
# embedder refuses to guess. A positive integer sets the exact count; -1 sizes
# to the host's core count (availableParallelism) — an explicit "match cores"
# directive, still your choice, not a fallback. Dedicated box: -1 or the core
# count. Shared / low-RAM host: a small number. Unset, empty, 0, or malformed →
# crash on load.
# Example: PLURNK_EMBED_WORKERS=-1   (or a positive integer, e.g. 8)
PLURNK_EMBED_WORKERS=
